
1. Codebase Structure
file-system-monitor/
├── .github/
│   ├── workflows/                # GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD
│   │   └── ci.yml                # Workflow for testing, linting, and deployment
├── docs/                         # Documentation (e.g., README, API docs)
│   ├── README.md                 # Project overview and usage instructions
│   ├── CONTRIBUTING.md           # Guide for contributors
│   └── CHANGELOG.md              # Track changes across versions
├── src/                          # Core source code
│   ├── __init__.py               # Makes src a package
│   ├── main.py                   # Entry point to start the monitoring tool
│   ├── monitor/
│   │   ├── __init__.py           # Makes monitor a package
│   │   ├── file_monitor.py       # File monitoring logic
│   │   ├── hash_checker.py       # File hashing and tampering detection
│   │   └── alert.py              # Alerting mechanisms (e.g., email, logs)
│   ├── utils/
│   │   ├── __init__.py           # Makes utils a package
│   │   ├── logger.py             # Logging configuration
│   │   └── config.py             # Configuration management
├── tests/                        # Unit and integration tests
│   ├── test_file_monitor.py      # Tests for file monitoring
│   ├── test_hash_checker.py      # Tests for hashing
│   └── test_alert.py             # Tests for alerting
├── .env                          # Environment variables (e.g., email credentials)
├── requirements.txt              # Python dependencies
├── setup.py                      # Setup script for packaging
├── Dockerfile                    # Docker configuration for containerization
├── docker-compose.yml            # Docker Compose for multi-container setups
├── Makefile                      # Automate common tasks (e.g., testing, linting)
├── LICENSE                       # License for the project
└── .gitignore                    # Files and directories to ignore in Git






